## ****Introduction to Functions****
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## **Task 1**
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Following code provides a functon to square a number. Enter the program into Eclipse or Repl.itand run it.

Modify the program to print the square of a few other numbers 10,5,35,4531

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
public class Main {

static int square(int x) {
return x = x * x;
	}

public static void main(String[] args) {
int myValue = square(10);
		System.out.println("10 Squared is " + myValue);
	}
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Solution**:

Takes in a user input and squares that instead

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {

static int square(int x) {
return x = x * x;
	}

public static void main(String[] args) {
Scanner myScan = new Scanner(System.in);
System.out.println("Enter a number to square:");
int input = myScan.nextInt();

System.out.println("Your number squared is: " + square(input));
	}
}

