## **Task 6**
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a function called shout that takes a String and return that string converted to uppercase and with an exclamation mark addded to the end.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
public static void main(String[] args) {

		String message = "Hello";
		System.out.println(message);
	}
```

So the above code would print `HELLO!` to the screen.

**Solution**:

```java
public class Main {

static String shout(String x){
 return x.toUpperCase();
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
  
System.out.println(shout("hello") + "!");

	}
}


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## **Task 7**
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a function called `longest` that takes two strings and returns the longest of the two strings.Such that `longest("Help","me")` would return `"Help"`.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Solution**:

```java
public class Main {

static String longest(String word1, String word2){
  if (word1.length() > word2.length()){
return word1;
  } else {
    return word2;
  }
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
String word1 = "Java";
String word2 = "Javascript";  
  System.out.println(longest(word1, word2) + " is the longest word");
	}
}


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## **Task 8**
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a function called longestShout that takes two strings and returns the longest of the strings converted to uppercase and with an exclamation mark appended to the string.Such that `longestShout("Help","me")` would return `"HELP!"`.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Solution**:

```java
public class Main {

static String longestShout(String word1, String word2){
  if (word1.length() > word2.length()){
return word1.toUpperCase() + "!";
  } else {
    return word2.toUpperCase() + "!";
  }
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
String word1 = "Java";
String word2 = "Javascript";  
  System.out.println(longestShout(word1, word2));
	}
}


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## **Task 9**
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Apply the `square` function to the numbers between 1 and 20 using a for loop.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Solution**:

```java
public class Main {

static int square(int x) {
  return x * x;     
	}

public static void main(String[] args) {
  for (int i = 0; i <= 20; i++){      System.out.println(square(i));

  }
	}
}


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## **Task 10**
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a program that asks the user for two numbers and then prints the maximum of the two numbers using your `max` function.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Solution**:

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {

static int max (int num1, int num2){
  if (num1 > num2){
    return num1;
  } else {
    return num2;
  }
}

public static void main(String[] args) {
Scanner myScan = new Scanner(System.in);
System.out.println("Enter a number");
int num1 = myScan.nextInt();  
System.out.println("Enter another number");
int num2 = myScan.nextInt();  
System.out.println("The biggest number is: " + max(num1, num2));  
	}
}
